## Types of configuration parameter values

Openstack API requires to store some database configuration parameter's values as strings, even if they contain numbers.
To force store their values as strings set <span pulumi-lang-nodejs="`stringType`" pulumi-lang-dotnet="`StringType`" pulumi-lang-go="`stringType`" pulumi-lang-python="`string_type`" pulumi-lang-yaml="`stringType`" pulumi-lang-java="`stringType`">`string_type`</span> to <span pulumi-lang-nodejs="`true`" pulumi-lang-dotnet="`True`" pulumi-lang-go="`true`" pulumi-lang-python="`true`" pulumi-lang-yaml="`true`" pulumi-lang-java="`true`">`true`</span>. Otherwise Terraform will try to store them as number what can cause error from Openstack API like below:
```
"The value provided for the configuration parameter log_min_duration_statement is not of type string."
```

