openstack:networking/portSecGroupAssocia.description:
Manages a V2 port's security groups within OpenStack. Useful, when the port was
not created by Terraform (e.g. Manila or LBaaS). 

When the resource is deleted, Terraform doesn't delete the port, but unsets the
list of user defined security group IDs.  However, if <span pulumi-lang-nodejs="`enforce`" pulumi-lang-dotnet="`Enforce`" pulumi-lang-go="`enforce`" pulumi-lang-python="`enforce`" pulumi-lang-yaml="`enforce`" pulumi-lang-java="`enforce`">`enforce`</span> is set to <span pulumi-lang-nodejs="`true`" pulumi-lang-dotnet="`True`" pulumi-lang-go="`true`" pulumi-lang-python="`true`" pulumi-lang-yaml="`true`" pulumi-lang-java="`true`">`true`</span>
and the resource is deleted, Terraform will remove all assigned security group
IDs.

> **Warning:** This resource should **not** be used when the
port was created directly within Terraform. If it is, it can lead  
to **security problems** with incorrect security groups on ports

## Example Usage

### Append a security group to an existing port

<!--Start PulumiCodeChooser -->
